 narrative practice, Klapproth presents detailed textual analyses of Anglo-Western and Australian Aboriginal oral narratives, and contextualizes them with respect to the different storytelling practices, values and worldviews in both cultures. Narrative as Social Practice offers new insights to students and specialists in the fields of narratology, discourse analysis, cross-cultural pragmatics, anthropology, folklore study, the ethnography of communication, and Australian Aboriginal studies.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aAboriginal AustraliansvFolklore. 0aDiscourse analysis, NarrativezAustralia. 0aDiscourse analysis, NarrativezEnglish-speaking countries. 0aOral traditionzAustralia. 0aOral traditionzEnglish-speaking countries. 0aStorytellingzAustralia. 0aStorytellingzEnglish-speaking countries. 4aAustralien. 4aErzählen. 4aGesprochene Sprache. 4aSprachsoziologie. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aAustralia.  aSociology of Language.  aSpoken Language.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Linguistics and Semiotics 2000 - 2014z9783110636970oZDB-23-DLS08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDe Gruyter Mouton Backlist 2000-2015z978311074296108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2009z9783110219517oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PACKAGE ENGLISH LANGUAGES TITLES 2009z978311021952408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PACKAGE ENGLISH LINGUISTICS 2009z978311021954808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET LINGUISTIK UND LITERATURWISSENSCHAFT  2009z9783110219470oZDB-23-DGA0 cprintz978311018136440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311019742640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110197426423Coveruhttps://